        <dc:title>Parent-Based Treatment as Efficacious as Cognitive Behavioral Therapy for Childhood Anxiety: A Randomized Noninferiority Study of Supportive Parenting for Anxious Childhood Emotions</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>This randomized noninferiority study found SPACE to be noninferior to CBT for childhood anxiety, with reductions in family accommodation and parenting stress in both arms and greater accommodation reduction with SPACE. It is the core efficacy paper for SPACE, but it is not an independent replication because it comes from the Yale/Lebowitz line of work.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2019</dc:date>
