        <dc:title>Psychological stepped care for anxious adolescents in community mental health services: A pilot effectiveness trial</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>A pilot RCT in community mental health services found stepped care used less therapy time with similar clinical benefits and quality-adjusted life years versus treatment as usual. The abstract frames stepped care as promising, but the study was small and did not test a whole public-health system.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2021</dc:date>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
                <rdf:value>https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/e8b04d4fb3707ec7c1f40cbe66cd3fd6f85f53fe</rdf:value>
            </dcterms:URI>
        </dc:identifier>
    </bib:Article>
