        <dc:title>Stepped-care versus therapist-guided, internet-based cognitive behaviour therapy for childhood and adolescent anxiety: A non-inferiority trial</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>This preregistered noninferiority trial found stepped-care internet CBT was noninferior to therapist-guided internet CBT at 12 weeks and 9 months. It supports one stepped-care delivery variant, but not a complete integrated model spanning universal, targeted, and specialist tiers.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2023</dc:date>
