                </rdf:li>
            </rdf:Seq>
        </bib:authors>
        <dc:title>The Efficacy and Cost-Effectiveness of Stepped Care Prevention and Treatment for Depressive and/or Anxiety Disorders: A Systematic Review and Meta-Analysis</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>This systematic review and meta-analysis included 10 randomized controlled trials of stepped-care prevention and treatment for depressive and/or anxiety disorders. It found stepped-care treatment outperformed care as usual for anxiety symptoms, but it still stops short of evaluating a complete universal→targeted→specialist care system in youth anxiety.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2016</dc:date>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
