                       <foaf:surname>J. Morris</foaf:surname>
                    </foaf:Person>
                </rdf:li>
            </rdf:Seq>
        </bib:authors>
        <dc:title>Child &amp; adolescent anxiety and family accommodation : exploring the role of cognitive coping</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Adolescents’ passive social-media exposure, feedback monitoring, and problematic use were associated with higher anxiety in a cross-sectional sample. The study also reported small moderation effects involving stress and sleep quality, but it did not test family accommodation as part of the model.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2019</dc:date>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
                <rdf:value>https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/0e8d0dc961d0596f1f821d12dd3a0a3a7e2c86e6</rdf:value>
