        <dc:title>Cross‐sectional and longitudinal associations of screen time with adolescent depression and anxiety</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>In the Future Proofing cohort, screen time was associated with anxiety cross-sectionally, but the longitudinal association with anxiety was null and the depression association was small. This argues against a strong direct causal effect of screen time on later anxiety in adolescents.</dcterms:abstract>
