        <dc:title>Phenomenology and clinical correlates of family accommodation in pediatric anxiety disorders.</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>In anxious youth, family accommodation was common and associated with greater anxiety severity, externalizing behaviors, and functional impairment. The paper did not include digital exposure measures, so it informs the accommodation side of the question only.</dcterms:abstract>
