        <dc:title>Parental emotion socialization and internalizing problems in childhood and adolescence: A meta-analytic review</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>This meta-analytic review found supportive parental emotion socialization was very weakly negatively associated with child internalizing problems (r=-.06), while nonsupportive behaviors were moderately positively associated (r=.18).</dcterms:abstract>
