        <dc:title>Mothers' symptoms of anxiety and depression and the development of child temperament: A genetically informative, longitudinal investigation</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Using MoBa (mothers n=34,060; offspring n=42,526), this genetically informed longitudinal study examined associations between maternal anxiety/depression symptoms and child temperament, finding small stable correlations and minimal co-development over time.</dcterms:abstract>
